sentenceList.stringAnnotated: The Apollo spacecraft had three parts: a Command Module with a cabin for the three astronauts, and the only part that landed back on Earth<Ent>; a Service Module, which supported the Command Module with propulsion, electrical power, oxygen, and water; and a Lunar Module for landing on the Moon.<S><Ent> After being sent toward the Moon<Ent> by the Saturn V's upper stage, the astronauts separated the spacecraft from it and traveled for three days until they entered into lunar orbit.<S> Armstrong and Aldrin then moved into the Lunar Module and landed in the Sea<Ent> of<Ent> Tranquility.<S><Ent> They stayed a total of about 21.5 hours on the lunar surface.<S> After lifting off in the upper part of the Lunar Module and rejoining Collins in the Command Module, they returned to Earth<Ent> and landed in the Pacific<Ent> Ocean<Ent> on July 24.<S>
